cs.NE, cs.LG, cs.CV, cs.AI, q-bio.NC

Reasoning: 
- cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing) is the most likely category as the paper deals with neuronal cell-type classification using deep learning models.
- cs.LG (Machine Learning) is also likely as the paper employs deep learning models for the classification task.
- cs.CV (Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition) is a possible category as the dataset used in the paper is obtained with calcium imaging techniques, which is a type of image-based measurement.
- cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) is another possible category as the paper deals with automated classification using machine learning models.
- q-bio.NC (Neurons and Cognition) is a possible category as the paper deals with neuronal cell-type classification, which is a topic related to neuroscience.
